VE_STR1(Desc_mm512_mask3_fnmsub_round_ps, "Multiply packed single-precision (32-bit) floating-point elements in a and b, subtract packed elements in c from the negated intermediate result, and store the results in dst using writemask k (elements are copied from c when the corresponding mask bit is not set).  Rounding is done according to the rounding[3:0] parameter, which can be one of:    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEAREST_INT |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC) // round to nearest, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEG_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round down, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_POS_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round up, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_ZERO |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)        // truncate, and suppress exceptions\n    _MM_FROUND_CUR_DIRECTION                       // use MXCSR.RC; see _MM_SET_ROUNDING_MODE\n\nFOR j := 0 to 15\n\ti := j*32\n\tIF k[j]\n\t\tdst[i+31:i] := -(a[i+31:i] * b[i+31:i]) - c[i+31:i]\n\tELSE\n\t\tdst[i+31:i] := c[i+31:i]\n\tFI\nENDFOR\t\ndst[MAX:512] := 0")
