VE_STR1(Desc_mm512_mask_mul_round_pch, "Multiply packed complex numbers in a and b, and store the results in dst using writemask k (elements are copied from src\n when the corresponding mask bit is not set). Each complex number is \ncomposed of two adjacent half-precision (16-bit) floating-point \nelements, which defines the complex number complex = vec.fp16[0] + i * vec.fp16[1].\n\t\tRounding is done according to the rounding[3:0] parameter, which can be one of:    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEAREST_INT |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC) // round to nearest, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEG_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round down, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_POS_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round up, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_ZERO |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)        // truncate, and suppress exceptions\n    _MM_FROUND_CUR_DIRECTION                       // use MXCSR.RC; see _MM_SET_ROUNDING_MODE\n\nFOR i := 0 to 15\n\tIF k[i]\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+0] := (a.fp16[2*i+0] * b.fp16[2*i+0]) - (a.fp16[2*i+1] * b.fp16[2*i+1])\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+1] := (a.fp16[2*i+1] * b.fp16[2*i+0]) + (a.fp16[2*i+0] * b.fp16[2*i+1])\n\tELSE\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+0] := src.fp16[2*i+0]\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+1] := src.fp16[2*i+1]\n\tFI\nENDFOR\ndst[MAX:512] := 0")
VE_STR1(Desc_mm512_maskz_mul_round_pch, "Multiply packed complex numbers in a and b, and store the results in dst using zeromask k\n (elements are zeroed out when the corresponding mask bit is not set). \nEach complex number is composed of two adjacent half-precision (16-bit) \nfloating-point elements, which defines the complex number complex = vec.fp16[0] + i * vec.fp16[1].\n\t\t\tRounding is done according to the rounding[3:0] parameter, which can be one of:    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEAREST_INT |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC) // round to nearest, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEG_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round down, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_POS_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round up, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_ZERO |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)        // truncate, and suppress exceptions\n    _MM_FROUND_CUR_DIRECTION                       // use MXCSR.RC; see _MM_SET_ROUNDING_MODE\n\nFOR i := 0 to 15\n\tIF k[i]\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+0] := (a.fp16[2*i+0] * b.fp16[2*i+0]) - (a.fp16[2*i+1] * b.fp16[2*i+1])\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+1] := (a.fp16[2*i+1] * b.fp16[2*i+0]) + (a.fp16[2*i+0] * b.fp16[2*i+1])\n\tELSE\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+0] := 0\n\t\tdst.fp16[2*i+1] := 0\n\tFI\nENDFOR\ndst[MAX:512] := 0")
VE_STR1(Desc_mm512_mul_round_pch, "Multiply packed complex numbers in a and b, and store the results in dst.\n Each complex number is composed of two adjacent half-precision (16-bit)\n floating-point elements, which defines the complex number complex = vec.fp16[0] + i * vec.fp16[1].\n\t\t\tRounding is done according to the rounding[3:0] parameter, which can be one of:    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEAREST_INT |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC) // round to nearest, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_NEG_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round down, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_POS_INF |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)     // round up, and suppress exceptions\n    (_MM_FROUND_TO_ZERO |_MM_FROUND_NO_EXC)        // truncate, and suppress exceptions\n    _MM_FROUND_CUR_DIRECTION                       // use MXCSR.RC; see _MM_SET_ROUNDING_MODE\n\nFOR i := 0 to 15\n\tdst.fp16[2*i+0] := (a.fp16[2*i+0] * b.fp16[2*i+0]) - (a.fp16[2*i+1] * b.fp16[2*i+1])\n\tdst.fp16[2*i+1] := (a.fp16[2*i+1] * b.fp16[2*i+0]) + (a.fp16[2*i+0] * b.fp16[2*i+1])\nENDFOR\ndst[MAX:512] := 0")
